<br>
Come to think of it, just what is the mana savings through specialization, anyways?  (Says the guy with the under-30 cleric for his main, does it show?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 436<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/02 8:23:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has there been any specialization+focus research done?</span><hr size=1> It is known that (at a minimum), the summoned earring stacks with specialization. From that it is logical to conclude that the permanent mana reduction items do as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1719<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/02 3:54:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has there been any specialization+focus research done?</span><hr size=1> Every 20% in specialization reduces the mana cost of appropriate spells by 1%, and stacks with various focus items.<br>
